nch culture really means today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aNational characteristics, French. 0aPopular culturezFrance. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / French.2bisacsh  aFrance.  aFrench culture.  alanguage styles.  amarket.  apolitical ideologies.  apopular culture.  asocial context.  asongs.  astate policy.1 aArmstrong, Nigel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Diana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLooseley, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLooseley, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMazdon, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlatten, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez9783111283630oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130266423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130266/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPc1986d2013